laboratory_examinations.findings: The tumor was composed of non-keratinizing squamous cell carcinoma (SCC) and large cell neuroendocrine carcinoma (LCNEC). The SCC part was positive for p63 and negative for synaptophysin, chromogranin-A, CD56, and insulinoma-associated protein 1 (INSM1). The LCNEC part was focally reactive with synaptophysin, CD56, and INSM1, but negative for p63 and chromogranin-A.
